BT 0 g /F2 22 Tf 210.96 700 Td (HOW TO PLAY KAKURO) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 13 Tf 72 640 Td (Kakuro is a number crossword puzzle:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 13 Tf 72 600 Td (1. Fill white cells with digits 1-9.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 13 Tf 72 575 Td (2. Numbers in each run must add up to the clue number.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 13 Tf 72 550 Td (3. No digit can repeat within a single run.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 13 Tf 72 525 Td (4. A 'run' is a group of consecutive white cells \(across or down\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 480 Td (Reading the Clues:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 12 Tf 72 450 Td (- Dark cells contain clue numbers with a diagonal line.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 12 Tf 72 425 Td (- The number ABOVE the diagonal = sum for the column below.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 12 Tf 72 400 Td (- The number BELOW the diagonal = sum for the row to the right.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 360 Td (Difficulty: EASY \(6x6 and 7x7 grids\)) Tj ET

endstream
